"{\n  \"description\": \"Technician (Track Maintenance) at Network Rail\",\n  \"howToApply\": \"To apply for this role, please click on the 'Apply Now' button on the job advert page. You will be asked to complete an application form and provide your CV and a cover letter. Once you have submitted your application, you may be required to complete pre-screening questions and undergo pre-employment checks.\",\n  \"aboutTheRole\": {\n    \"essential\": [\n      \"Experience of arranging and implementing safe systems of work\",\n      \"Knowledge of how to organise and control the safe and efficient delivery of work\",\n      \"Strong communication skills, both in person and in writing\",\n      \"Knowledge of discipline-specific maintenance, inspection, faulting, and renewal techniques\",\n      \"Willing and able to work shifts in all weathers\",\n      \"Meet the required benchmark for application screening questions (all applicants)\"\n    ],\n    \"desirable\": [\n      \"Leadership experience\",\n      \"Relevant qualification (NVQ Level 1 or 2)\",\n      \"Previous rail experience\",\n      \"Safety-focused and respectful of rules\",\n      \"Problem-solving skills\",\n      \"Willingness to learn and develop skills\"\n    ],\n    \"keyAccountabilities\": [\n      \"Maintain, inspect, and repair the track network to keep the railway safe and efficient\",\n      \"Work outdoors in all conditions, at all times of the year, day or night\",\n      \"Lead the team when asked by the team leader\",\n      \"Deliver work safely and check the team has the right competencies to meet strict safety standards\",\n      \"Role model safe working behaviors and challenge any potential risks to safety\",\n      \"Consistently develop skills and competencies relevant to the discipline\",\n      \"Actively seek continuous learning and self-development\",\n      \"Hold an NVQ Level 1 or 2 linked to the discipline or have equivalent relevant experience\"\n    ]\n  }\n}"